abstract = {The microgrid system combines smart grid technology with distributed energy resources. The uncertainty and intermittency of distributed energy resources, coupled with the volatility of electricity demand and the power market, pose significant challenges to the microgrid energy management system. In this paper, a reinforcement learning based microgrid management system is put forward to achieve maximal economic returns. A microgrid incorporating components such as price-responsive loads is proposed to enhance demand flexibility and balance the uncertainty of distributed energy generation. Proximal policy optimization algorithm, combined with semi-deterministic training, is adopted to acceletare the RL convergence process and improve the performence of the agent. In addition, the effectiveness of the management system is verified through the simulation, ultimately achieving satisfactory economic benefits.},
